text:
Create a new column in each data frame from above called status


Exp_list$treatment$status&lt;-character(20)
Exp_list$placebo$status&lt;-character(10)


For the non-placebo data frame (within the list), create a for loop and use if/then/else logic to create the status column’s values.


for (i in 1:20) {
  if (Exp_list$treatment$post_bp[i] &lt;= 120) {
    Exp_list$treatment$status[i] &lt;- "optimal"
  } else if (Exp_list$treatment$post_bp[i] &gt; 120 & Exp_list$treatment$post_bp[i] &lt;= 130) {
    Exp_list$treatment$status[i] &lt;- "borderline"
  } else if (Exp_list$treatment$post_bp[i] &gt; 130) {
    Exp_list$treatment$status[i] &lt;- "high"
  } else {
    Exp_list$treatment$status[i] &lt;- 'error'
  }
}


Repeat for the placebo data frame (within the list).


for (i in 1:10) {
  if (Exp_list$placebo$post_bp[i] &lt;= 120) {
    Exp_list$placebo$status[i] &lt;- "optimal"
  } else if (Exp_list$placebo$post_bp[i] &gt; 120 & Exp_list$placebo$post_bp[i] &lt;= 130) {
    Exp_list$placebo$status[i] &lt;- "borderline"
  } else if (Exp_list$placebo$post_bp[i] &gt; 130) {
    Exp_list$placebo$status[i] &lt;- "high"
  } else {
    Exp_list$placebo$status[i] &lt;- 'error'
  }
}
